[1] Haiti
Date: Sat 10 May 2014
Source: Crofsblogs [edited]
http://crofsblogs.typepad.com/h5n1/2014/05/dr-carroll-on-possible-chikungunya-in-haiti.html#comment-6a00d83451bd6d69e201a3fd05a245970b


Dr. John Carroll has sent this email and allowed it to be posted here [in Crofsblogs]:

"Yesterday [9 May 2014], I visited an orphanage in Port-au-Prince where we adopted our boy a few years ago.

There are currently 97 children in the orphanage. During the last 7-10 days, 24 of the kids and 5 of the adult staff have come down with a febrile illness. With their fevers, they have headaches, joint pain, and chest pain, and general malaise.

I examined a number of these kids yesterday [9 May 2014] and from a clinical standpoint, they have signs and symptoms consistent with chikungunya [virus infections]. I could find no focus of infection on any of them, i.e. no pharyngitis, enlarged nodes, pulmonary rales, etc.

We have no lab tests to prove or disprove chikungunya [virus infections]. (And to be honest, if I would have examined this same group of kids a month ago, chikungunya would never have made my list on the differential.)

--
Communicated by:
Roland Hubner
Superior Health Council
Brussels
Belgium
<roland.hubner@sante.belgique.be>

[The outbreak in Haiti appears to be intensifying and spreading. The 12 May 2014 edition of the Haiti Press Network (http://www.hpnhaiti.com/site/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=12700:haiti-sante-des-cas-de-chikungunya-diagnostique-dans-le-sud&catid=8:societe&Itemid=14 [in French]) stated that of the 60 cases of chikungunya virus infection diagnosed or identified, 10 specimens were transferred to the National Laboratory for extensive testing. Laboratory tests have shown that more than 7 cases are due to infection with chikungunya virus, while several others are still under investigation.

ProMED thanks David Haman (<david.hawman@ucdenver.edu>) for submitting a similar report.

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map showing the location of Haiti and the Dominican Republic can be accessed at https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=2467601,24. - Mod.TY]

