[4] St. Lucia
Date: Wed 7 May 2014
Source: You Tube [video, summ. & edited]
http://www.youtube.com/watch?feature=player_embedded&v=HMQ66r1FHOk


Health authorities are confirming increased cases of the mosquito-borne virus, chikungunya but say it is not confined to a particular geographical area.

The Island's Chief Medical Officer says there are now 5 confirmed cases of the virus, and the Environmental Health department is taking measures to reduce its spread. There are 25 suspected in addition to the 5 confirmed cases. The distribution of cases on the island is widespread, with 2 confirmed cases in the north and 2 in the south.

